AlternateHistoryHub's Mu video was my main inspiration for the shape and location of it. Admittedly I'm terrible with geology and generally handwave the effects fictional landmasses might have on climate, yes it might completely mess up entire weather systems but I think it's fine to embrace inherently unrealistic ideas if it makes for a good narrative.
>And the diseases
My thinking is along the lines of Sergals having vague relations and trade with other Polynesians and potentially even South Americans based on its location prior to Spanish contact in a not!Torres expedition, so they might have already built up a resistance to some diseases along with the genus gap. All of this is still fairly early in development but I do want to explore these ideas further since the story I have in mind does deal with their collective history.

Most stories I see either explore the idea of Anthros either existing in what's essentially our modern unchanged world or suddenly appearing after some event, and I would like to explore the alternative of how their discovery might affect parts of our history. Them being Sergals is just for fun wanting to use them while not raising the question of coexisting with their feral counterparts.
